                Watcharin is a professor in the Information Technology Division at Maejo University in Chiangmai,
                Thailand. He has an educational background, starting with a Diploma in Electrical, Major in Technique
                Computer from Rajamangala Institute of Technology, Northern Campus, Chiang Mai, Thailand in 1996.
                Watcharin earned a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science from Payap University, Chiangmai, Thailand in
                1998, and a Master's degree in Software Engineering from Chiangmai University, Chiangmai, Thailand in
                2008. In 2022, Watcharin earned his Ph.D. in Computer Science from Chiangmai University, Thailand. With
                years of industry experience, Watcharin has worked as a mobile game developer at Jimmysoftware Co., Ltd
                from 2001 to 2004, and as a developer at RoundBxo Co., Ltd from 2006 to 2010. Since 2012, Watcharin has
                been a dedicated lecturer in the Information Technology Division at Maejo University, where he has made
                significant contributions to the field.
                </br> </br> <span style="color: #B20102">Watcharin's major areas of research interests and
